From 25b66d4390dec396663ef34b02f5afacbfec8c48 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: "copilot-swe-agent[bot]" <198982749+Copilot@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Sun, 17 May 2026 06:58:53 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] ath9k: correctly handle short radar pulses

Commit 3c0efb745a17 ("ath9k: discard undersized packets") set the lower
bound for RX packet length to 10 bytes (min ACK size) to filter out
garbage frames. However, short radar pulses are reported as PHY_ERROR
frames with rs_datalen == 3, so they were being silently discarded.
This breaks DFS radar detection.

Fix by adding a PHY_ERROR exception to the size check: if the frame is
a PHY error, allow it through even if rs_datalen < 10.  Zero-length
packets are still unconditionally discarded.

Based on upstream commit df5c4150501e ("ath9k: correctly handle short
radar pulses").

Co-authored-by: HiGarfield <32226909+HiGarfield@users.noreply.github.com>
---
 drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath9k/recv.c | 5 ++++-
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath9k/recv.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath9k/recv.c
@@ -827,8 +827,11 @@ static int ath9k_rx_skb_preprocess(struc
 
 	/*
 	 * Discard zero-length packets and packets smaller than an ACK
+	 * which are not PHY_ERROR (short radar pulses have a length of 3)
 	 */
-	if (rx_stats->rs_datalen < 10) {
+	if (!rx_stats->rs_datalen ||
+	    (rx_stats->rs_datalen < 10 &&
+	     !(rx_stats->rs_status & ATH9K_RXERR_PHY))) {
 		RX_STAT_INC(rx_len_err);
 		goto corrupt;
 	}
